<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/18122999-kandie-sweeney"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1398779109i/18122999._UX100_CR0,5,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/18122999-kandie-sweeney">Kandie Sweeney</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The Angels Game is technically NOT a prequel. The books can, and are meant to be. read independent of each other so can be read in any order. They hav<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The Angels Game is technically NOT a prequel. The books can, and are meant to be. read independent of each other so can be read in any order. They have characters that cross over each story. I got this straight from the author's web site. I have read two of the 3 books, and am excited to get to the last one. He is an amazing author. If you skip some of this book, it isn't going to have much effect when you read the last one I wouldn't think. I'd try and hang with the book though. It is craziness at its best.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
