  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2732703382" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5858203-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1520844755p2/5858203.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2732703382?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/5858203-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20207924-the-angel-s-game">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2732703382" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7399904335663244727">Popsugar Challenge 2020 - A book set in the 1920&apos;s <br/><br/>It&apos;s really confusing to what this book actually is. Some seem to say its a prequel to Shadow of the Wind while others say its book two in the Cemetery of Forgotten Books series but neither of those descriptions feel right to me, having now read it I would say its a companion novel to the CoFB series. This can be read as a separate entity to the series and as a standalone. There is no overarching theme that connects this to the other books other</span>
  <span id="freeText7399904335663244727" style="display:none">Popsugar Challenge 2020 - A book set in the 1920's <br /><br />It's really confusing to what this book actually is. Some seem to say its a prequel to Shadow of the Wind while others say its book two in the Cemetery of Forgotten Books series but neither of those descriptions feel right to me, having now read it I would say its a companion novel to the CoFB series. This can be read as a separate entity to the series and as a standalone. There is no overarching theme that connects this to the other books other than this is set in Barcelona and the epilogue vaguely tries to tie it to the series but the string is loose. <br /><br />Once again the author creates a vivid 1920's Barcelona where the streets although dark come alive. The author is known for his world building and this book doesn't disappoint on that but I really wasn't into the plot or characters in this one. This book is a mix of gothic mystery with paranormal elements which on the whole didnt work for me, the pacing of mysteries are too slow to hold my attention and this is definitely a slow burn. <br /><br />3 stars, the world building and language were enough to see me through.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7399904335663244727" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


